<description>Retrieves the current status of a customer’s loan application.

The action first attempts to identify the customer using available authenticated session context (such as ContactId or AccountId). If a valid identifier is found, the system retrieves all loan applications associated with that customer.

If no authenticated context is available, the agent requests the customer’s registered email address and uses it to locate the customer record and associated loan applications.

If multiple loan applications are found, the agent presents a list and prompts the user to select the specific application they want to check. Once selected, the system retrieves and returns the status of that application.

If multiple loan applications are found, the agent presents a list and prompts the user to select the specific application they want to check. Once selected, the system retrieves and returns the status of that application.

If no loan applications are found, the system returns a message informing the user that no applications were found for the provided details.</description>
