<fullName>Loan_Status_179d30000002nXh</fullName>
<description>Use this version:

Retrieves the status of an existing customer loan application.

Use this action only when at least one valid customer identifier is already available:

authenticated session context that can identify the customer, such as ContactId or AccountId, or

the customer’s registered email address provided in the conversation.

Do not invoke this action until the required customer identifier is available.

If the customer cannot be identified from authenticated session context, first ask the user for the email address used for the loan application and wait for the user to provide it before invoking the action.

If multiple loan applications are found, the action returns the available application options and the user must choose one before the status is retrieved.

If exactly one loan application is found, the action returns the application status.

If no loan applications are found after a valid lookup, the action returns a no-results message.

This action is only for retrieving the status of existing loan applications. It must not be used for creating, updating, or submitting applications.</description>
